    },
    {
      "datasource": { "type": "loki", "uid": "loki" },
      "description": "Shows `sms_otp` JSON logs from the `api` compose service. **Request ID**, **Correlation ID**, **SMS ID**, and **Provider message ID** use LogQL `|=` (literal substring on the raw JSON line). Leave a field **empty** to apply no filter on that dimension (empty `|=` matches all lines). Paste `X-Request-ID` / `X-Correlation-Id`, internal `sms_id`, or provider `provider_message_id` values or substrings. Field-exact in Explore: `{compose_service=\"api\"} | json | sms_id=\"<id>\"` or `provider_message_id=\"<id>\"`.",
      "gridPos": { "h": 14, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 43 },
      "id": 201,
      "options": {
        "dedupStrategy": "none",
        "enableLogDetails": true,
        "prettifyLogMessage": true,
        "showCommonLabels": false,
        "showLabels": true,
        "showTime": true,
        "sortOrder": "Descending",
        "wrapLogMessage": true
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": { "type": "loki", "uid": "loki" },
          "editorMode": "code",
          "expr": "{compose_service=\"api\"} |= \"$request_id\" |= \"$correlation_id\" |= \"$sms_id\" |= \"$provider_message_id\" | json | line_format \"{{.time}} {{.level}} {{.msg}} method={{.method}} path={{.path}} status={{.status}} latency_ms={{.latency_ms}} request_id={{.request_id}} correlation_id={{.correlation_id}} sms_id={{.sms_id}} provider_message_id={{.provider_message_id}} event={{.event}} recovery_kind={{.recovery_kind}}\"",
          "queryType": "range",
          "refId": "A"
        }
      ],
      "title": "API logs by request_id, correlation_id, sms_id & provider_message_id",
      "type": "logs"
    },
    {
      "datasource": { "type": "loki", "uid": "loki" },
      "description": "Problems from `api` JSON logs: **(A)** `slog` **WARN** or **ERROR** (e.g. `sms_callback_failed`, GORM/SQL issues). **(B)** access lines `msg=http_request` with **HTTP status ≥ 500** (still `level=INFO` on the line). Recovery `sms_recovery_event` stays INFO—use the full API logs panel. Plain `level=ERROR` alone was empty because many failure paths used WARN. **Msg** (`$msg`) filters this panel only via LogQL `|=` substring on the raw line (matches the JSON `msg` field, e.g. `register_failed`, `sms_callback_lookup_failed`); leave empty for no filter.",
      "gridPos": { "h": 12, "w": 24, "x": 0, "y": 57 },
      "id": 202,
      "options": {
        "dedupStrategy": "none",
        "enableLogDetails": true,
        "prettifyLogMessage": true,
        "showCommonLabels": false,
        "showLabels": true,
        "showTime": true,
        "sortOrder": "Descending",
        "wrapLogMessage": true
      },
      "targets": [
        {
          "datasource": { "type": "loki", "uid": "loki" },
          "editorMode": "code",
          "expr": "{compose_service=\"api\"} |= \"$msg\" | json | level=~\"WARN|ERROR\" | line_format \"{{.time}} {{.level}} {{.msg}} method={{.method}} path={{.path}} status={{.status}} request_id={{.request_id}} correlation_id={{.correlation_id}} sms_id={{.sms_id}} event={{.event}} err={{.err}}\"",
          "queryType": "range",
          "refId": "A"
        },
        {
          "datasource": { "type": "loki", "uid": "loki" },
          "editorMode": "code",
          "expr": "{compose_service=\"api\"} |= \"$msg\" | json | msg=\"http_request\" | status >= 500 | line_format \"{{.time}} {{.level}} {{.msg}} method={{.method}} path={{.path}} status={{.status}} latency_ms={{.latency_ms}} request_id={{.request_id}} correlation_id={{.correlation_id}}\"",
          "queryType": "range",
          "refId": "B"
        }
      ],
      "title": "API problems (WARN/ERROR + HTTP 5xx access)",
      "type": "logs"
    }
  ],
